&lt;p&gt;The best way to understand our Engineering team is in their own words — here’s how they describe their work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;On the Engineering team at Bonfire, it is about more than code. For us, it&#39;s essential to build a deep understanding and intuitive sense of what makes our game special through our players&#39; hearts and minds. Guided by this sensibility, we form close partnerships with artists and designers to challenge ourselves, exploring creative and fun ways to evolve the game together. We ruthlessly prioritize what matters most and continually weigh trade-offs in our pursuit of making both playing and building our game feel great.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Principal/Lead Systems Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;, you will play a central role in shaping the foundational technology powering Arkheron, our first game and a cross-platform competitive multiplayer title. This role demands deep experience building systems for competitive multiplayer games, where engine performance, hardware constraints, and platform characteristics have a direct impact on responsiveness and player experience.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are at a transformative stage in our engine technology, and we are looking for someone to help shape its development toward data-centric principles; to make Arkheron feel great to play for players, and great to build for our developers through fast and reliable iteration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
